              <p>
                I am Pavan Kumar, a fourth year undergraduate student in the <a href='www.iitm.ac.in'>Indian Institute of Technology Madras</a>. I am currently pursuing a Bachelors degree in the department of Mechanical Engineering. My interests lie in Continuum Mechanics, especially Solid Mechanics, Mechanics of Materials and Molecular Dynamic simulations.
<br>
<br>
<h5>Hobbies</h5>
            	<p>I spend my free time reading detective fiction and fantasy novels. I love reading Agatha Christie novels, especially those featuring Hercule Poirot, as she never fails to surprise you with her twisted plots. Of late, I have also started to explore the fantasy genre, thanks to Brandon Sanderson. He is an amazing story-teller, and his perfect blend of drama, romance, suspense and twists ensure that you never keep the book down.</p>
		<p>I also love listening to Carnatic music, though it is a recent addition to my list of hobbies. Cryptic crosswords also interest me. I never fail to attempt the crossword that appears in the Indian english daily, The Hindu.</p> 
